1. *Kapija* je otvorena. (The gate is open.)
2. Vidim *kapiju* na kraju puta. (I see the gate at the end of the road.)
3. Polako prolazim kroz *kapiju*. (I'm slowly passing through the gate.)
4. Pogledaj tu lepu *kapiju* na kući! (Look at that beautiful gate on the house!)
5. *Kapija* se ne može zatvoriti. (The gate can't be closed.)
6. Ograda je postavljena oko *kapije*. (The fence is set around the gate.)
7. Vidiš li onu *kapiju* na parkingu? (Do you see that gate in the parking lot?)
8. Moram otići do *kapije* da otvorim. (I have to go to the gate to open it.)
9. *Kapija* je pokrivena snegom. (The gate is covered with snow.)
10. Stavio sam novu bravu na *kapiju*. (I put a new lock on the gate.)

Note: The word "kapiju" is in the accusative case in sentences 2, 3, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, and 10, while it is in the nominative case in sentences 1 and 4.